    <stitle>HENDRICKSON HN-460 SUSPENSION - MAINTENANCE - REBOUND CONTROL ASSEMBLIES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REBOUND CONTROL ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <para>The adjustable rebound bumper assembly prevents the overextension of the bolster springs during vehicle
            operation. For proper suspension operation, this assembly must be adjusted after the body is installed and
            prior to being put in service (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0301111">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0301111" figsize="col-wide">
